Part E: Word Problems

Write an equation and solve.

A ribbon is 12.6 meters long. A craft project uses 3 pieces of ribbon that are each 2.4 meters long. How much ribbon is left?

A runner jogs 4.75 miles each day for 6 days. How many miles does the runner complete in total?

A bakery sold 95.4 pounds of flour in the morning and 48.75 pounds in the afternoon. How many pounds were sold altogether?

A 3.5-meter board is cut into pieces that are each 0.25 meters long. How many full pieces can you make?